From Mellodew Subject Re If There Were No Hell In article M shellgate Larry Overacker writes Here's a question that some friends and I were debating last Q If you knew beyond all doubt that hell did not exist and that unbelievers simply remained dead would you remain a Christian My contention is that if you answer this question with I would not then remain a Christian then you really are not one Following Jesus Christ has everything to do with sharing in his work and spreading the news that the Kingdom of Heaven is already among Fear based religion is not a faith relationship with the One Who made us So does that mean that anyone who is a Christian to avoid Hell isn't really a Christian at all It sounds like it to Mit Liebe in Christus Martyn Martyn Mellodew E mail Department of Applied Mathematics ARPA Internet and Theoretical Physics JANET The University of Liverpool Box Liverpool England Dubito ergo Deus '